Vice President Mike Pence visited Grand Forks Air Force Base in North Dakota to express his gratitude and respect to the men and women serving in the United States Armed Forces. He brought greetings from President Donald Trump and thanked the families who support the service members. Pence commended the leadership at the base and recognized the important role it plays in national security. He highlighted the administration's efforts to rebuild and support the military, including the largest increase in national defense spending in decades. Pence urged the service members to stay ready and continue their important work, assuring them of the support and prayers of the American people. The visit concluded with a prayer for the safety and guidance of the service members.